                                      &= 13 \times 18 \\\\
                                      &= 234 \ \text{cm}
\end{aligned}
$

If the height increased by $25 \%$, then the new height will be $100 + 25 = 125 \%$ of the previous height. Using that, we get

$
\begin{aligned}
